body:
Harry Styles in a leopard print suit, designed by Calvin Klein. London (night two) 2018 (photo courtesy of @justharried)

Valerie Leon wearing just a small selection of Biba’s Leopard print line, a two piece suit. (I also included a promo pic of Twiggy wearing the matching coat, because, well… look at it!)

Biba was a London fashion store of the 1960s and 1970s. Biba was started and primarily run by the Polish-born Barbara Hulanicki with help of her husband Stephen Fitz-Simon. (If you’re a loser like I am, and are interested in quirky stores, be sure to look up the Biba department store!)

question: CEO Harry working late one!!
answer:
Harry sighed as his head rested in his hands. He rubbed his face a bit. All he could think about was his girlfriend cosied up on the sofa in a big blanket waiting for him to come and snuggle, yet it was 9PM and he was still working in his sky scraper building going over millions of emails, phone calls, notes and anything else that passed his desk. He desperately wanted to go home. So desperately.


After a bout ten minutes a small knock was heard at his office door. He was alone in his building except security so who on earth could that be. Before he knew it, his girlfriend opened the door and walked in and he let out a breath of relieve. “Hey Mr CEO” she smiled. He got up and opened his arms for hug and she quickly placed her bags on his desk and embraced him. “Hey” he whispered into his neck. She pulled away to cup his face in her hands. He looked exhausted. She knew that he was working himself so hard but his face is starting to show it. “H, you look awful, have you been drinking?” She asked. “Coffee?” Y/N tutted. “Told you that you need to start drinking water, coffee is the reason you get those awful headaches.” He lecturered. He smiled knowing she was right and knowing that she cared. “I’m sorry baby” he pressed a kiss to her plump lips hoping it would be enough to justify his dehydration.


Y/N released herself from his grip and pulled out her goodies out her back. 2 bottles of 1.5 litres of water, a baking tray with what smelt like a pasta bake, chocolate buttons (Harry’s favourite) and a pot of olives. “What’s all this?” He laughed. “Knew you wasn’t looking after yourself so, I took the liberty of sorting you out.” He smiled. “I love you” he said looking at his perfect girlfriend. “I love you too, now eat” she played.


With Y/N sitting on his lap after finishing their makeshift dinner they cuddled for a bit. “Anything I can help you with, get you home early?” She offered “actually, can you reply to his emails, if they need to see my my schedule is on the other tab.” He smiled “I just have to read these” he continued holding up papers.


After an hour or so of working they walked out of Styles Co, fed, hydrated and even more in love.
